        <h2>Common Issues with MoTak Ice Machines</h2>
        <p>Regular maintenance and timely repairs are crucial for keeping your MoTak ice machine running smoothly. Common problems include:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Ice machine not making ice</strong> – Often caused by a clogged water filter, faulty water inlet valve, or a failing compressor.</li>
            <li><strong>Slow ice production</strong> – Due to low water pressure, dirty condenser coils, or an improperly functioning thermostat.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice machine leaking water</strong> – Can result from broken hoses, improper drainage, or a defective water pump.</li>
            <li><strong>Ice cubes are too small or irregular</strong> – Typically due to a malfunctioning water inlet valve or incorrect water flow settings.</li>
            <li><strong>Excessive noise from the machine</strong> – Worn-out fan motors, failing bearings, or loose components.</li>
        </ul>
        
